In the case where θ = 180°, the contributions of the D+A− and LE states to the CT absorptions act in a destructive fashion. As a result, the D+A− and LE-state contributions cancel each other, especially in the low-energy tail (see also Fig. 2a). As the tD+A--LE\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
